      "content": "it's just that even if i go to a therapist, the reality stays the same. the debt is still there, the failed project is still there, and the feeling of being a total failure doesn't just go away because i talked about it. i feel like i've been trying to fix a broken engine for years and i'm just out of parts. everything feels so permanent, like this heaviness is just who i am now. i just want a way to actually escape the noise, not just talk about it. i wish there was a way to just... opt out. to just find some stillness that actually lasts.",
